{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1113.erdos_1113 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1113.erdos_1113.","id":"vf_006a8650521c9cc9","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1113: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. A positive odd integer $m$ such that none of $2^km+1$ are prime for $k\\geq 0$ is called a Sierpinski number. We say that a set of primes $P$ is a covering set for $m$ if every $2^km+1$ is divisible by some $p\\in P$.\n\nAre there Sierpinski numbers with no finite covering set of primes? Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and Graham \\cite{ErGr80} asked whether there are Sierpinski numbers for which a covering system is not 'responsible', for which the best interpretation seems to be the above question. They also prove that for every $l\\geq 1$ there is an $m$ such that $2^km^i+1$ is composite for all $1\\leq i\\leq l$ and $k\\geq 0$. Prize: no. OEIS: A076336. Tags: covering systems, number theory.","id":"vf_931e48bcad60f899","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"attempted via frontier 'difference/covering' (transfer_strength=weak) -> no_progress","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_ce0a12da4f17e783","kind":"dead_end","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"difference/covering","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_ce0a12da4f17e783","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca15973f38386a512f1f8fa66bbae72bb1b9acb1daf2e669ab279c7"}],"dependency_impact":"problem_local","detail_url":"problems/1113.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Sig